
Active Directory Live Class — Part 2

Pre-Class Requirements & Setup Instructions

To ensure the class runs smoothly and we maximize learning time, all students must complete the required setup BEFORE the class begins. 
We will NOT pause the class for system setup.

Please read carefully and complete ALL prerequisites prior to showtime.

---

## ⏰ Early Access (For Students Using Our Hosted Virtual Machines)

If you purchased or plan to use virtual machines provided by us, the classroom will open 1 hour before the official class start time.

During this early-access window, we will:

- Create your VM account  
- Assign your lab machines  
- Verify login and connectivity  
- Ensure both systems are working properly  
- Provide a quick Proxmox walkthrough (if needed)  

⚠️ Important

- VM setup assistance is ONLY available during the early access hour.  
- Once the class officially starts, we will begin immediately.  
- Late VM setup requests may not be accommodated.  

---

🖥️ Students Using Their Own Systems (Local Lab Setup)

If you are running your lab locally, your environment **MUST be fully prepared before class begins.

You may use any virtualization platform:

- Proxmox (recommended for lab alignment)
- Hyper-V
- VMware Workstation / ESXi
- VirtualBox

---

Required Lab Environment

You MUST have TWO working virtual machines ready before class:

1. Windows Server 2025
This will be used for:
- Active Directory Domain Services
- DNS
- Group Policy
- AD administration tasks

2. Windows 11 Pro
This will be used for:
- Domain joining
- Client management
- GPO testing
- User & policy validation

---

Recommended System Requirements

To run both VMs smoothly:

- Minimum 16 GB RAM (32 GB recommended)
- 4+ CPU cores
- 100+ GB free disk space
- Hardware virtualization enabled (VT-x / AMD-V)

---

VM Preparation Checklist

Before class, confirm the following:

- [ ] Virtualization platform installed and working  
- [ ] Windows Server 2025 VM created  
- [ ] Windows 11 Pro VM created  
- [ ] Both operating systems fully installed  
- [ ] Both VMs boot successfully  
- [ ] Network connectivity verified  
- [ ] Administrator login confirmed on both systems  
- [ ] System performance is stable  
- [ ] Snapshots created (recommended)  

